The well-hidden Cave at the Hermit in the woods near Nový Bor was not actually habitable
In the north of Bohemia, in the foothills of the Lusatian Mountains, near Nový Bor in the Českolipsko region, in the forests through which the Count's Road led, there are several sandstone rock formations.
Both natural and man-made.
And we will go after the man-made hand.
The place is called the Cave at the Hermit.
In fact, no hermit ever lived here and the cave served as a shelter, more precisely a shelter chamber, probably for grain.
The cave is carved from the side into a rocky promontory and accessible by stairs from above.
At the same time, however, it is practically invisible until the last moment.
It is revealed only by the narrow stairs leading to a kind of rock gallery, from where you enter the rock.
Although it seems that the chamber is quite far from human habitation, at the time of its creation there may have been a field on the plateau where there is a forest today.
"The fact that the building does not have a window and no firebox located in the traditional place clearly proves that no hermit could ever survive the winter here," explains historian Kamil Podroužek from the Faculty of Arts of Jan Evangelista Purkyně in Ústí nad Labem.
The single-room building has only a stone bench at the back, apparently used for storing containers.
"I see it as a chamber for storing some food or products from the field," adds Kamil Podroužek.
On the walls of the cave there are traces of tools.
Breaking off the sandstone with a canine was quite simple and fast for those in the know.
It was enough to use the joints appropriately and gradually break off the sandstone.
According to the length of the canine track and the method of mowing in general, it is possible to determine the period of origin of the cave.
According to the historian, it is probably the end of the 18th century.
The cave is freely accessible and, according to the mess that appears in it, someone sometimes sleeps there these days.
If you approach the cave from above from one of the forest paths and you will be attracted by the flowing stream and the nearby count's path under the cave, you will certainly find the trail down as well.
And on the way out of the forest, you may be captivated by the nearby Raven Rocks.
