Viper bite: The little girl ended up in the hospital!
"This year's first case was recorded in the Železná Ruda region.
A viper bit a girl in the leg, born in 2010, who was brought by her parents to the local ambulance base," Mária Svobodová, a regional spokeswoman for the emergency medical service, told Deník, adding that the child was then transported to the hospital in Klatovy.
The viper is the only poisonous snake in the Czech Republic and it is in Šumava that these animals occur in higher numbers, so it is good to be careful during walks.
However, there is no great danger from these animals.
The chance that you will be bitten by a viper is not very high, during normal contact it is afraid of itself.
And if she has the space to do so, she likes to crawl away with a loud hiss.
It will only attack if it feels threatened a lot - for example, if you accidentally step on it.
Even her bite is not a tragedy, its venom is very effective against small mammals, but it does not kill humans.
This can happen only if a person has a particularly weakened organism, or suffers from an allergy.
The risk of danger is therefore mainly in children, the elderly and allergy sufferers.
"A person often feels nauseous, sweats, has an elevated temperature, thirst, abdominal pain and diarrhea, and anaphylactic shock can occur in weakened individuals and especially allergy sufferers," Miriam Gredová from the Klatovy hospital told Deník.
