Storm Hanna Reaches Texas Coast
Hurricane Hanna arrived on the southwest coast of the US state of Texas on Saturday afternoon local time (before midnight CEST overnight).
It hit Padre Island, Texas, about 24 miles north of Port Mansfield, and weakened to a tropical storm as it moved over land.
However, according to meteorologists, it still poses a great danger to the inhabitants of coastal areas.
It brought with it strong winds and intense rainfall; along with localized flooding, power outages and various material damage, including damaged ships, have been reported, according to the Associated Press.
Texas Gov. Greg Abbott on Saturday declared a state of natural disaster for 32 counties in southwest Texas and advised people to voluntarily evacuate.
The strongest warning was received by people from the coastal strip between Port Mansfield and Mesquite Bay, but in total the element is expected to hit an area of almost 500 kilometers before gradually moving over northeastern Mexico.
"Although Hanna is now a tropical storm, heavy rain and wind, sea level rises, dangerous surf and isolated tornadoes could pose a threat," the U.S. National Hurricane Center (NHC) warned.
This morning local time (afternoon CEST), the storm moved in the area of the US-Mexico border and was accompanied by winds of 85 kilometers per hour.
Hanna on Saturday became the first hurricane of this year's hurricane season in the Atlantic region.
Over the Gulf of Mexico, it was accompanied by winds of up to 145 kilometers per hour, but it gradually weakened to 112 kilometers per hour as it advanced to land, which again eliminated Hanna from the category of hurricanes.
Authorities urged locals to wait out the storm at home, not forgetting hygiene measures to prevent the spread of coronavirus.
Texas is one of the US states most affected by the covid-19 pandemic.
Due to the existing safety measures and the need to maintain social distancing, possible evacuations are also a major challenge.
Makeshift shelters were opened in hotels, schools and gymnasiums.
In Hidalgo County, Texas, one of the buildings was also adapted to shelter evacuees who tested positive for the coronavirus or were otherwise exposed to the virus.
Local authorities urged all evacuees to bring masks and disinfectant gels to the shelter if possible.
"It's not over yet.
We expect catastrophic flooding," said Chris Birchfield, who works for the National Weather Service (NWS) in Brownsville.
Forecasts say that in some places up to 300 millimetres of rain could fall in a few hours, in some cases almost 500 millimetres, which, together with the rise in sea level, could flood many coastal settlements.
Zeman to confer the rank of general on Colonel Lipka
On Wednesday, President Miloš Zeman will confer the rank of general on Colonel Pavel Lipka.
This is the result of an overview of expected events of the Ministry of Defense.
The reason for conferring the rank of brigadier general is Lipka's appointment in August as deputy commander of the alliance's multinational division northeast in Poland.
Lipka still serves as Deputy Commander of the Land Forces of the Czech Army.
Zeman's promotion was proposed by the government at the end of June.
From the beginning of August, Lipka will replace Brigadier General Karel Řehka as deputy commander of the Multinational Division Northeast in Elblag, Poland, which commands units of the alliance's forward presence in Poland and the Baltics.
In March, Řehka became the director of the National Cyber and Information Security Agency (NÚKIB).
The government suggested to the president that he give Lipka the rank of brigadier general.
According to the Act on Professional Soldiers, a higher rank may be conferred on a soldier for the duration of an elected office or for the period of performance of a service task required by the conferring of a higher rank.
The post of deputy commander of an alliance division corresponds to the rank of general.
A soldier who has been awarded the rank has the same rights and obligations as if he had been appointed to that rank.
However, he is not entitled to an adjustment of salary corresponding to the rank.
The conferral of the rank lasts until the reason for which it was granted ceases to exist.
"Colonel Lipka demonstrates high professional preparedness and is a role model for subordinates.
It significantly participates in the performance of the tasks of the Armed Forces of the Czech Republic, including cooperation with foreign partners and ensuring the participation of the army in foreign operations," the Ministry of Defence said in June about the proposal for promotion.
Wednesday's promotion will take place at 12:30 p.m. at Prague Castle, attended by Minister of Defense Lubomír Metnar and Chief of General Staff Aleš Opata.
