A woman spent hundreds of thousands of infirm son's disability pension.
She faces trial
The money that the 33-year-old receives from the state as a disability pension is intended primarily to improve his quality of life.
The woman faces up to eight years in prison for embezzlement.
Due to his poor health, the court deprived the sick man of legal capacity and appointed his mother as a guardian who, among other things, was to manage her son's money.
"Between mid-November 2013 and January this year, the woman used part of the funds from her son's disability pension for her own needs, depriving him of CZK 440,000," police spokeswoman Dana Ladmanová said, adding that the accused woman was aggravated by the fact that, as a guardian, she had a specially imposed duty to defend the interests of the injured party.
