Heat threatens in Czech Rep from Tuesday, meteorologists warn of fires
Meteorologists' warnings of high temperatures apply for Tuesday afternoon for the whole of Bohemia with the exception of the Karlovy Vary region and also for southern and central Moravia.
"Exceptionally, temperatures can exceed 34 degrees Celsius, especially in Central Bohemia," they say.
People are advised to keep a drinking regime in the heat and limit their physical load at noon and afternoon.
Due to the warm weather with minimal rainfall, there will be a risk of fires from Tuesday morning.
Windy weather could contribute to their rapid spread.
Meteorologists' warnings about the risk of fires apply to Central Bohemia, including Prague, Liberec, Ústí nad Labem, Karlovy Vary and Pilsen.
A fire warning will remain in effect until further notice.
"We do not expect significant rainfall, which would mitigate the danger, in the northwest and west of Bohemia at least until the end of the week," the CHMI said.
Prague City Hall responded to the meteorologists' warnings by banning fires in risky places, which is to apply from Tuesday.
People in the capital will not be allowed to set open fires in, for example, parks, gardens or forests, up to 50 meters from the edge of the forest.
Smoking and the use of pyrotechnics is also prohibited in these places.
The measure will apply until further notice, Prague City Hall spokesman Vít Hofman said.
